pt.ist.fenixframework.consistencyPredicates

Class DomainDependenceRecord

  • java.lang.Object
    • pt.ist.fenixframework.core.AbstractDomainObject
      • pt.ist.fenixframework.consistencyPredicates.DomainDependenceRecord_Base
        • pt.ist.fenixframework.consistencyPredicates.DomainDependenceRecord
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, jvstm.cps.DependenceRecord<DomainMetaObject>, DomainObject

    public class DomainDependenceRecord
extends DomainDependenceRecord_Base
implements jvstm.cps.DependenceRecord<DomainMetaObject>
    A DomainDependenceRecord represents the result of the execution of a consistency predicate method for a dependent domain object. The DomainDependenceRecord has a set of depended DomainMetaObjects, that represent the other domain objects that were read to execute the consistency predicate. If any of these objects is modified, the consistency predicate must be reexecuted.

    A DomainDependenceRecord will never register the dependent object as a depended object. After executing a consistency predicate, a DomainDependenceRecord will not even be created if:
    • the object does not depend on other objects, and
    • the object is consistent

      • delete

        public void delete()
        Deletes this DomainDependenceRecord after disconnecting it from all relations.
        A DomainDependenceRecord can be deleted in two cases:
        • When the dependent object is being deleted. In this case, its DomainMetaObject will also be deleted, and will therefore invoke this method.
        • The DomainConsistencyPredicate was removed from the code. In this case, we only remove the link to all the meta objects, which are not deleted.
